{{Infobox football league season | competition = [[Lebanese Football League]] | season = 1974-75 | winners = '''[[Al-Ansar FC|Al-Ansar]]''' | relegated = [[Al Tadamon Beirut]] [[Nejmeh SC|Al-Nejmeh]] | continentalcup1 = [[1988–89 Asian Club Championship]] | continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[Al-Ansar SC]] | continentalcup2 = | continentalcup2 qualifiers = | league topscorer = {{flagicon|Lebanon}} [[Fouad Saad]] (6) | biggest home win = | biggest away win = | highest scoring = | matches = | total goals = | prevseason = [[Lebanese Football League 1974–75|1974–75]] | nextseason = [[Lebanese Football League 1989–90|1989–90]] }}
Statistics of [[Lebanese Football League]] in the 1987/1988 season.
This is the final table recognised by the Lebanon FA, of the Lebanese first league championship after 13 years of war in the country. Crowd trouble disrupted many games; [[Al-Safa' SC|Safa]], [[Salam Zgharta]], [[Shabab Al-Sahel]] and [[Al-Shabiba Mazraa]] were all docked 4 points, while [[Al-Tadamon Beirut]] and [[Nejmeh SC|Al-Nejmeh]] withdrew.
==Overview== [[Al-Ansar FC|Al-Ansar]] won the championship, the first in 13 years after the [[Lebanese Civil War]]
