{{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Estádio Mundunduleno | image = | location = [[Luena, Moxico Province|Luena]], [[Moxico Province|Moxico]], [[Angola]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = {{Start date and years ago|2006|11|13}} | renovated = {{Start date and years ago|2013|4|18}} | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[F.C. Bravos do Maquis]] | operator = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[F.C. Bravos do Maquis|Bravos do Maquis]] | seating_capacity = 4,300 }} '''Estádio Jones Cufune Mundunduleno''' is a football [[stadium]] in [[Luena, Moxico Province]], [[Angola]].
It is owned by [[F.C. Bravos do Maquis|Futebol Clube Bravos do Maquis]] and holds 4,300 people.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.angop.ao/angola/pt_pt/noticias/desporto/2017/1/5/Girabola2017-Munduduleno-tem-luz-verde-FAF,75375631-6eaa-47c7-b2e0-7b16c4c61e63.html |title=Girabola2017: Munduduleno tem "luz verde" da FAF |publisher=ANGOP.com |date=5 Feb 2017 |accessdate=5 Feb 2017 |language=pt}}</ref>
==History== The Stadium was named after Jones Cufune Mundunduleno, a MPLA commander and guerrilla fighter from eastern Angola.
==Location== Mundunduleno is located at the Mandembwe neighborhood, around 2&nbsp;km from the city of [[Luena, Moxico Province|Luena]], in an area surrounded by eucalyptus trees.
In 2013, the Stadium underwent a major renovation which forced the home team to play its home games at the neighboring Estádio das Mangueiras in the province of Lunda Sul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.angop.ao/angola/pt_pt/noticias/desporto/2013/2/9/Obras-Mundunduleno-transferem-Maquis-para-Saurimo,6ce17c02-b2d3-4629-8638-4e66540b3933.html |title=Obras no Mundunduleno "transferem" Maquis para Saurimo |publisher=ANGOP.com |date=2 Mar 2013 |accessdate=5 Feb 2017 |language=pt}}</ref>
