{{notability|Films|date=February 2018}} {{refimprove|date=February 2018}} {{Infobox film | name = First Match | image = First Match.png | alt = | caption = Film poster | director = Olivia Newman | producer = {{Plainlist| * Chanelle Elaine * Veronica Nickel * Bryan Unkeless }} | writer = Olivia Newman | starring = {{Plainlist| * Elvire Emmanuel * [[Yahya Abdul-Mateen II]] * [[Colman Domingo]] * Jharrel Jerome * Jared Kemp }} | music = | cinematography = Ashley Connor | editing = Tamara Meem | studio = Clubhouse Pictures | distributor = [[Netflix]] | released = {{Film date|2018|3|12|[[South by Southwest]]|2018|3|30|Netflix}} | runtime = 102 minutes | country = United States | language = English | budget = | gross = }}
'''''First Match''''' is a 2018 American [[drama film]] written and directed by Olivia Newman, based on her 2010 short film of the same name. The film stars Elvire Emanuelle, [[Yahya Abdul-Mateen II]], [[Colman Domingo]], Jharrel Jerome, and Jared Kemp. The film premiered at the 2018 [[South by Southwest]] festival on March 12 where it won the Audience Award and the LUNA/Gamechanger Award. It was then released on [[Netflix]] on March 30, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2018/01/31/netflix-announces-new-films-documentaries-and-docu-series-to-debut-at-the-2018-sxsw-film-festival-771112/20180131netflix03|title=Netflix Announces New Films, Documentaries and Docu-Series to Debut at the 2018 SXSW Film Festival|date=January 31, 2018|work=[[The Futon Critic]]}}</ref>
==Cast== * Elvire Emanuelle as Monique * [[Yahya Abdul-Mateen II]] as Darrel, Monique’s father * [[Colman Domingo]] as Coach Castile * Jharrel Jerome as Omari * Jared Kemp as Malik
==Reception== On [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 84%, based on 19 reviews, and an [[average rating]] of 7.3/10.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/first_match |title=First Match (2018) |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango Media]] |accessdate=April 13, 2018}}</ref>
